<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🔁 M001 Week 2 — English Worksheet (Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Loops · <strong>Course:</strong> Pyramid Problems · <strong>Level:</strong> Beginner · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read the steps. Circle your answer.</p>
<pre><code>repeat 3 times:
    place block down
    move forward
</code></pre>
<p><strong>How many blocks does the agent place? Circle one:</strong> 1 · 3 · 9</p>
<p><strong>Line or tower? Circle one:</strong> line · tower</p>
<pre><code>repeat 4 times:
    place block down
    move up by 1
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Is this a line or a tower? Circle one:</strong> line · tower</p>
<p><strong>How tall is it? Circle one:</strong> 2 · 4 · 8</p>
<hr />
<h2>2 · Find the Difference 🐛</h2>
<p>Clean steps first, then a buggy version. Circle the bug.</p>
<p><strong>Pair A</strong> — Should place a row of 4 blocks.</p>
<pre><code># clean
repeat 4 times:
    place block down
    move forward
</code></pre>
<pre><code># buggy
repeat 4 times:
    place block down
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? Circle one:</strong> all 4 blocks land in one spot · they form a line · they form a tower</p>
<p><strong>Pair B</strong> — Should build a tower 4 blocks tall.</p>
<pre><code># clean
repeat 4 times:
    place block down
    move up by 1
</code></pre>
<pre><code># buggy
repeat 4 times:
    place block down
    move forward
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? Circle one:</strong> it builds a flat line, not a tower · it builds a taller tower · nothing happens</p>
<hr />
<h2>3 · Fill the Gap ✏️</h2>
<p>Build a row of <strong>5 blocks</strong> with a loop. Fill the missing number and line.</p>
<pre><code>repeat ____ times:
    place block down
    ____________
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Missing number? Circle one:</strong> 5 · 2</p>
<p><strong>Missing line? Circle one:</strong> move forward · turn right</p>
<hr />
<h2>4 · Show Your Work 📸🎥</h2>
<p>Now switch to your homework world. Use a loop to build a <strong>10-block straight wall</strong>. When you finish, come back here.</p>
<p>Record <strong>one video</strong> (a phone is fine). Show two things:</p>
<p><strong>1 · Your code.</strong> Scroll through it. Say what each part does.</p>
<p><strong>2 · Your build.</strong> Point the camera. Name the parts.</p>
<p>Fill the blanks:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Today I built ______.</p>
<p>I built it using this code: ______.</p>
<p>In this code I used ______.</p>
<p>The hardest part was ______.</p>
<p>That part was hard because ______.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write your lines here, then say them in your video.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
